    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-06-05T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-06-05T06:00:00-05:00" n="91"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d91">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A4 General Committee/953: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chairman of the American Delegation</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Davis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-06-05T12:00:00+01:00"
                            >June 5, 1934—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received June 5—7:27 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>871. My 868, June 4, 10 p.m. The situation appears so tense today that I have
                    decided not to present the resolution sent you last night <pb facs="0202"
                        n="102" xml:id="pg_102"/> unless I can get agreement between the British and
                    French before doing so.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
